  OPT_STRING('t', "very-long-option-name-that-exceeds-buffer-capacity-"
                  "and-causes-overflow-with-many-characters-here", 
             &some_var, "help", "ARGUMENT_WITH_VERY_LONG_NAME_HERE"),
  OPT_END()
};

// Calling args_print_usage(malicious_options, 20) triggers overflow
```

## 9. Severity Assessment

**CRITICAL**

- **Impact:** Stack buffer overflow → arbitrary code execution
- **Exploitability:** High (requires control over option definitions or ability to influence them)
- **Scope:** Local privilege escalation or code execution
- **CVSS v3.1 Base Score:** 8.8 (High)

## 10. Recommended Fix

Replace all `sprintf()` calls with `snprintf()`:

```c
void args_print_usage(
    args_option_t *options,
    int help_alignment)
{
  char buffer[128];
  int remaining;

  for (; options->type != ARGS_OPT_END; options++)
  {
    int len = snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "  ");
    remaining = sizeof(buffer) - len;

    if (options->short_name != '\0')
      len += snprintf(buffer + len, remaining, "-%c", options->short_name);
    else
      len += snprintf(buffer + len, remaining, "     ");

    remaining = sizeof(buffer) - len;
    if (options->short_name != '\0' && options->long_name != NULL)
      len += snprintf(buffer + len, remaining, ",  ");

    remaining = sizeof(buffer) - len;
    if (options->long_name != NULL)
      len += snprintf(buffer + len, remaining, "--%s", options->long_name);

    remaining = sizeof(buffer) - len;
    if (options->type == ARGS_OPT_STRING || options->type == ARGS_OPT_INTEGER)
    {
      snprintf(buffer + len, remaining, "%s%s",
          (options->long_name != NULL) ? "=" : " ",
          options->type_help);
    }

    printf("%-*s%s\n", help_alignment, buffer, options->help);
  }
}
```
